Data Masking** or **Advanced Masking Solution**.  \n2. Enforce 1-year log retention policies for audit trails.  \n\n---\n\n### 4. **Data Breach Notification (16.7%)**  \n**Risk Level:** Moderate  \n**Implications:** Delayed or incomplete notifications may violate the 72-hour DPDP mandate.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Standardize breach notifications with impact descriptions and mitigation steps.  \n2. Automate internal escalation workflows to meet deadlines.  \n\n---\n\n### 5. **Data Retention & Erasure (62.5%)**  \n**Risk Level:** Moderate  \n**Implications:** Non-secure erasure risks data leaks and non-compliance.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Automate erasure workflows using **Informatica’s NIST 800-88-compliant tools**.  \n2. Adopt DoD 5220.22-M standards for irreversible deletion.  \n\n---\n\n### 6. **Data Accuracy (0.0%)**  \n**Risk Level:** Critical  \n**Implications:** Inaccurate data undermines trust and violates DPDP principles.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Deploy **Informatica Cloud Data Quality** for automated profiling and cleansing.  \n2. Replace manual logs with **Informatica Log Analyzer** for audit trails.  \n\n---\n\n### 7. **Third-Party Processing (0.0%)**  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Implications:** Unsecured vendor agreements risk chain-of-trust breaches.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Revise contracts to mandate DPDP Section 6(1)(f) safeguards.  \n\n---\n\n### 8. **Cross-Border Transfers (16.7%)**  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Implications:** Unauthorized transfers may trigger regulatory action.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Enforce localization policies via **Informatica Cloud Data Governance Catalog**.  \n2. Monitor transfers with **Informatica Cloud Data Privacy Management**.  \n\n---\n\n## Strategic Recommendations  \n1. **Prioritize Critical Gaps:** Address Data Accuracy and Third-Party Processing first.  \n2. **Leverage Automation:** Use **Informatica’s suite** (e.g., Data Privacy Management, Cloud Data Quality) to replace manual processes.  \